						               													<description>Abszol&amp;uacute;t k&amp;eacute;ptelen sztorik is the third game in the word-and story-related Abszol&amp;uacute;t series published by book and game publisher Pagony.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In the game box you'll find 30 two-sided story cards (with 9 elements of a story, numbered), 9 number cards, cards to vote for each player, a notebook and a story book.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Draw one of the number cards. Everyone looks at their story card and writes the first (in later rounds, next) sentence for the story. They read it aloud and players vote with cards (0 to 3 points) for the best sentence (including their own). The sentence that gets the highest score will be written in the storybook. The player who wrote this sentence scores 3 points, everyone else scores as many points as the number they assigned to the winning player.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Keep writing the story this way, eventually using all the number cards. (For a shorter game, only certain numbers are used.) The player with the most points total wins, but of course it's the story that you've written together that matters.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
